Also, (O, TA,) accord. to IAạr, (O,) A red clay or earth: and i. q. magorapN [i. e. red ochre]; 
as also XarofN↓: accord. to Lth, a kind of trees, having a red dye: and said to be the same as 
[the Pers.] dAr PrnyAn [i. e. daAro ParoniyaAn, meaning Brazil-wood, which is commonly called in Arabic baq-am]. (O, TA:* in the former of which, the Pers. word here mentioned is written without the points to the P; and in the latter, AldAbrnyAn.)

