XaEiyrN, (Ṣ, Mṣb, Ḳ,) which may be also pronounced XiEiyrN, agreeably with the dial. of Temeem, as may any word of the measure faEiylN of which the medial radical letter is a faucial, and, accord. to Lth, certain of the Arabs pronounced in a similar manner any word of that measure of which the medial radical letter is not a faucial, like kabiyrN and jaliylN and kariymN, (MF,) [and thus do many in the present day, others pronouncing the fet-ḥ in this case, more correctly, in the manner termed UimaAlap, i. e. as “e” in our word “bed:” Barley;] a certain grain, (Ṣ, Mṣb,) well known: (Mṣb, Ḳ:) of the masc. gender, except in the dial. of the people of Nejd, who make it fem.: (Zj, Mṣb:) 
