XikaAkN 
Tents arranged in a row: (O, Ḳ:) one says, DarabuwA buyuwtahumo XikaAkFA They pitched their tents in one row: but accord. to Th, it is sikaAkFA, [q. v.], 
from Als-ik-apu. (TA.)

