5. tXw-r 
He had a deed done to him of which one should be ashamed. (Yaạḳoob, Th, A, Ḳ.) [It occurs in a saying of Yaạḳoob, respecting an indecent action of an Arab of the desert, app. as meaning His pudenda became exposed; 
