Also A certain kind of ridaMC 
[here meaning shawl], made in Cashmere and Lahore, and brought for sale to other countries; 
[erroneously] said to be made of camels' fur; and so called because raised to the shoulders, if it be an Arabic word [which is not the case, for it is from the Pers. XaAlN, whence our word “shawl”]: pl. XiylaAnN and XaAlaAtN. (TA.)

