4. AXAH, (Ṣ, A, Ḳ,) inf. n. UiXaAHapN, (IAạr, TA,) He was cautious, or in fear, (Ṣ, A, Ḳ,) minohu [of it], (A, TA,) i. e. a thing, or an affair, (TA,) and EalaI HaAjatihi [for the thing that he wanted]; (Ḳ;) 
as also XAyH↓, (Ṣ, A, Ḳ,) inf. muXaAyaHapN and XiyaAHN; 
and XaAHa↓: (Ḳ:) or he was cautious and in fear, endeavouring to repel death. (L.)

3. muXaAyaEapN primarily signifies The following another, or conforming with him, in, or as to, an affair, and an opinion; as also XiyaAEN; 
[an inf. n. of XAyEhu, like the former;] 
and so too signifies taXay-uEN↓ 
[if not a mistranscription for taXoyiyEN↓, which I rather think it to be, agreeably with what follows]: and the agreeing, or complying, with him, or obeying him. (TA.) 
You say, XAyEhu EalaI OamorK, (Lth, O, Mṣb, Ḳ,) inf. n. muXaAyaEapN (Mṣb) [and XiyaAEN], He followed him, or conformed with him, 
[&c.,] in, or as to, an affair: (Lth, O, Mṣb:) or he did so, and strengthened him; and likewise ElI raOoIK in, or as to, an opinion; 
as also Xy-Ehu↓ Ealayohi, referring to an opinion [and an affair]. (TA.) 
And maA tuXaAyiEuniI rijoliI walaA saAqiI My leg does not conform with [my wish] nor aid me to walk, nor does my shank. (TA.) 
And XaAyaEatohu nafosuhu EalaI celika His soul conformed [or complied] with him, [i. e. with his wish,] and encouraged him, to do that; 
as also Xay-aEatohu↓. (L, TA.)

